item.title: Lay off botting
item.dc:creator: @l3etal3lade l3etal3lade
item.description:
@l3etal3lade wrote:

True lesson here, script you’re own bot so its different from other bots, i know alot of current bots are semi randomized, but I’ve had goodluck I guess with a recordable bot (can’t macro every skill) but I’ve been able to raise mining from 28-85 in a week, fletching from like 55-87 in a day or two, and currently doing woodcut and firemaking. I just set it so it Only repeats the same action only 3-5 times in one hour, basically the bot records my actions for 12-20 mins After that it loops through those actions. And I do a shit ton of quests inbetween each bot session So it looks more realistic like I had a reason to stay botting certain skills. Again this won’t allow you to bot EVERY SKILL but has forked for me if you use the recordable bots in the right way you need to be careful about where you use them though and the camera angle you have set though, otherwise your bot will click random shit, and wonder off, for instance botting limestone, not many people go to that area often(great exp) but I could bot mining and crafting at once. set the action bar to items so you can drop/craft them or whatever. Works wonders. Just watch your bot as well after you set it to make sure the actions don’t screw up, this is not reccommended for botting combat skills and I haven’t tried anything else yet other than what I’ve noted, also the lower key you are the better, I was like I said dropping most of my items, I wasn’t keeping them to make money, which one one hand is bad but at least now I got high levels in those botted skills for when I want to make the money.

Read full topic
